posts.subject: Boudoir  October 2019
posts.body:
my first ever photo set on Patron. i choose this set, shot back in 2015 by Gregorio Campos, to be my first set on here as it was one of the first sets i ever really felt "sexy". i had always looked at my body as something androgynous and wanted to have curves with larger breasts. That idea of myself changed when i started modeling and realized that those things get in the way of being a "sample size" model. My small breast and thin frame actually worked to my advantage.
i was 23 when these photos where taken. i'm going to explain more in my next post for all my Tiers to see in more details of the personal experiences during this time in my life and my remission from my medical condition during this time.

posts.subject: Tokyo Love Hotel October 2019
posts.body:
shot by Cailin Hill in a 'Love hotel' in Tokyo, Japan.

Sneak peak into my world with the behind the scenes photos + editorial images. 


FUNNY story about this day! So in Japan they have these hourly hotels that people go to to either rest or take people to have sex ( facts). They are usually in the party districts and are small but all beautifully decorated in themes. Cailin choose this specific hotel to begin with, but they refused to let us enter as they could see we were trying to take photos and we where with a male makeup artist. Even after her Japanese husband came to talk to them it was apparent that they wanted nothing to do with us... SO, we went next-door where they happily let us enter this wood themed niche room. 

anywayyyyy, the problem was the doors where unable to open or close without a key.

so i was running from room to room to get my makeup done and we ended up locking the makeup artist in the room somehow and couldn't get him in for the actual shooting...LOL it was a very fun shoot.

this hotel is actually CLOSED DOWN NOW!!! :'(((((

posts.subject: Dark Dream ~
posts.body:
My country is on fire.

1 BILLION ANIMALS KILLED, 2000+ homes destroyed, 20m acres burned, 350m tonnes of CO2 released and 27 people killed...THIS is happening in my country :`(  And guess what? THE SUMMER HAS ONLY JUST BEGUN ... :`( :`(


My heart goes out to all the people, plants and animals effected by the fires ❤️

i thought i would dedicate this set i shot in 2017, out in the Victorian bushland, as it reminds me of the beauty of my country.
